Leaders have sent condolence messages to President Uhuru Kenyatta's family following the death of his sister Margaret Wambui.Wambui died aged 89 at a Nairobi hospital after a short illness. She was the only daughter and the eldest of two children of Mzee Kenyatta and his first wife Nyokabi.Wambui was a powerful figure in the Jomo Kenyatta presidency; she rose to become the mayor of Nairobi from 1970 to 1976.In 1976, she retired from county politics and was appointed Kenya's Permanent Representative to the United Nations Environmental Programme.In 1985, she was appointed Conference President during the UN Women's Conference held in Nairobi. Since then she has led a quiet life.She did not have children.More on this: Uhuru's elder sister Margaret Wambui dies aged 89National Assembly Majority leader Aden Duale eulogised Wambui as a dedicated and determined public servant who was well-regarded by all.Via Twitter, Foreign Affairs Cabinet Secretary Amina Mohamed prayed for fortitude for the family.Kiambu Governor William Kabogo wished the family peace and comfort.Musician Suzanna Owiyo also sent a condolence message.